From: Nama Abhinay <abhinay@example.com>
Date: Fri, 10 Jul 2026 05:31:52 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 1/3] Fix exposure detection to be banner-aware, not just
 port-based

has_web/has_ssh previously only checked static port numbers (80/443, 22),
so a web server on 8080 or an SSH service on a non-standard port went
undetected. Extracted the logic into scanner/classify.py so it can be
unit tested independently of the live scanning engine, and now checks
both port number and banner-identified product.
---
 main.py             | 13 ++++++++-----
 scanner/classify.py | 32 ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
 2 files changed, 40 insertions(+), 5 deletions(-)
 create mode 100644 scanner/classify.py

diff --git a/main.py b/main.py
index 9fdba03..c7f8eca 100644
--- a/main.py
+++ b/main.py
@@ -1,6 +1,7 @@
 import argparse
 from scanner.engine import threaded_scan
 from scanner.cve_lookup import extract_product_version, fetch_cves
+from scanner.classify import classify_exposure
 from scanner.splash import show_banner
 from utils.validator import validate_target
 from datetime import datetime
@@ -110,16 +111,18 @@ def main():
 
         tcp_ports.append(port)
 
-        if port in [80, 443]:
-            has_web = True
-        if port == 22:
-            has_ssh = True
+        product, version = (None, None)
